                Anemometer
            </h2>
            <p>
                An anemometer is a device that measures wind speed and direction. It is a common weather station
                instrument. The term is derived from the Greek word anemos (wind), and is used to describe any
                wind-speed instrument used in meteorology.
                The earliest known description of an anemometer was by Italian architect and author Leon Battista
                Alberti.

                The anemometer has changed little since its development in the 15th century. Alberti is said to have
                invented it around 1450.
            </p>

