            </h2>
            <p>
                A compass is a device that shows the cardinal directions used for navigation and geographic orientation.
                It commonly consists of a magnetized needle or other element, such as a compass card or compass rose,
                which can pivot to align itself with magnetic north.
            </p>
            <p>
